<br>
A small group of Wolves, consisting of Mandilloran, Jonan, Xinmakin, Hawkeyes and myself, led an assault on Mistmoore this eve. We decided that stealth would be our greatest asset, as we did not have a dedicated healer, so we crept through the hidden passageways beyond the graveyard and caught the Dark Elves in the pool room by surprise....or so we thought. One of the clever Vixens managed to locate Hawkeyes and call for help! Before we could react, the minions of Mayong were upon us. Noble was our fight, but the enemy was relentless...alas, we were forced to evacuate to the Greater Faydark. They had won that round, but the fight was not over...<br>
<br>
Again we assaulted the castle, gaining entry through the secret passageways. We entered the pool room and were able to catch the beasts off guard this time. Mandilloran and I lead the charge, with Hawkeys close behind, sword and axe flying, arcs of spellcraft racing in the air as we put to rest the Evil that infects that dark fortress. This time, we managed to defeat the first onslaught....but at a great cost. Hawkeyes and Xinmakin had fallen, Mandilloran was gravely wounded and I clung to life with but seven hit points to spare. Had it not been for the swift thinking of Jonan, master of the Elements, the day would have been lost.<br>
<br>
With the room taken, we were able to pause and rest from what was the most intense battle in all my years. Mandilloran, using his Paladin arts, revived the souls of Xinmakin and Hawkeyes, bringing our group to its full strength once more. From our base in the pool room, we were able to take Castle Mistmoore by force from the inside out! Nothing stood a chance against the bravery and honor of the Pack this night! Countless minions fell at our feet, including the Advisor who was dispatched quickly. Xinmakin was awarded his robe as a symbol of his bravery in combat. <br>
<br>
After what seemed like hours of searching without finding our goal, and just as we were starting to loose hope, the Shadow Knight Xicotl appeared before Hawkeyes, teeth glaring in the night. Quickly, we were upon him. In my rage of hate, I brushed off his Harm Touch without a flinch and struck again and again with my Longsword. At long last, the beast fell before my blade. In his posession I found the Glowing Hilt of Soulfire to nearly complete my quest for the holy sword of my ancestors. The time draws near when I will meet my destiny. Sir Lucan will fall by my blade, as Xicotl has this eve. With the help of my Pack, nothing will stand in my way... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/umandilloranwhitewolve.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandilloran Whitewolve</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/17/02 6:15:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvesfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.art.com/images/PRODUCTS/regular/10057000/10057350.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Xicotl has fallen!</span><hr size=1> Kronenburg well said! It was a glorious hunt that we five took this night and one that will always be remembered for me as the best of my Career.We were a little<br>
overwhelmed on the first assault but the lesson was quickly learned and we regrouped and got back in there and like no other battle I have ever seen or mayhaps again will, we gave no ground and held when the odds said no, this can not be won.Each of the 5 of us gave there all this night and to be sure there was valour enough to shake the very foundations of Evil Mistmore.When I am an old Man<br>
sitting around the fire pit of the Aegis Guild hall telling stories to anyone who will listen, this will be the one I tell most.What a night!!!<br>
